  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto mb-16">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 text-center">Why is the open network free?</h2>
    <div class="bg-white p-8 rounded-lg border">
      <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">Because the Intelligence Graph only works if people publish to it.</p>
      <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4">Every organization that publishes an OOS makes the network more valuable for every other organization. Gating publishing behind a paywall would kill the network before it reaches critical mass. That is the opposite of what we want.</p>
      <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4">The free tier is not a trial. It is not a limited version. It is the full product. Publish, browse, search, compare, discover intelligence, get morning briefings. Everything.</p>
      <p class="text-gray-700 font-medium">Enterprise exists for organizations that need the same capabilities behind their own walls. Private vault, internal graph, data isolation, compliance. That is a different problem with different requirements. That is where revenue lives.</p>
    </div>
