        <div class="px-6 pb-4 text-sm text-gray-600">Yes. The open network will always be free. We may add premium features in the future (advanced analytics, priority Scout scanning, white-label reports), but the core capabilities listed above will remain free.</div>
      </details>

      <details class="bg-white rounded-lg border group">
        <summary class="px-6 py-4 cursor-pointer font-medium text-sm flex items-center justify-between">
          Is my data used to train AI models?
          <svg class="w-4 h-4 text-gray-400 group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"/></svg>
        </summary>
        <div class="px-6 pb-4 text-sm text-gray-600">No. Published OOS files are used to power the Intelligence Graph (cross-org patterns, comparisons, recommendations). They are never sent to third-party AI models for training. Enterprise tier adds full data isolation.</div>
      </details>

      <details class="bg-white rounded-lg border group">
        <summary class="px-6 py-4 cursor-pointer font-medium text-sm flex items-center justify-between">
          What about sensitive information in my OOS?
          <svg class="w-4 h-4 text-gray-400 group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"/></svg>
        </summary>
        <div class="px-6 pb-4 text-sm text-gray-600">Every OOS is scanned for PII (client names, employee data, proprietary pricing) before publishing. Your org name is pseudonymized by default. The OOS captures coordination patterns and operational intelligence, not trade secrets. If something slips through, you can unpublish instantly.</div>
      </details>

      <details class="bg-white rounded-lg border group">
